The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | IITians get thrashed in hotel scuffle
                                                                                                            IITians get thrashed in hotel scuffle
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Kharagpur, Jan. 27: A Kharagpur hotel owner and some of his employees were arrested late tonight for allegedly beating up a group of IIT students who had gone there for dinner.         
	After the conclusion of Spring Fest, the institutes annual festival, 50 students went to the hotels restaurant-cum-bar around 8pm.         
	The 100-seater restaurant was three-fourths full and there was allegedly a fight among the students on which group would sit first. Waiters who intervened got embroiled in the argument, which snowballed into fisticuffs during a power cut around nine.        
	The students were thrown out of the hotel at 10pm.        
	Police refused to name the hotel or the accused, but confirmed that 11 persons had been arrested. There was an unruly incident and we took swift action, said subdivisional police officer Gaurav Sharma.        
	Professor D.K. Tripathi, the dean of student affairs, said the students were beaten up when they protested against the hotel employees misbehaviour. Two students were injured and treated at the hospital on the campus.        
	Plea for US security         
	Indian students in North America have sent an online petition to the Indian government to ensure their safety.        
	Abhijit Mahato, a PhD student of Duke University, North Carolina, was shot dead on Friday. His suspected killer, 19-year-old Stephen Lavance Oates, has been held without bond.                                                                                                                                                                            
